notesStmt.note: Repaired by Marty Dickson May 1980 (note in pencil first flyleaf recto at front of book).
Notes dated 1231, 1234 and 1269 A.H. recorded in ink (f. 1r).

msContents.summary: Complete, illustrated copy of the Shāhnāmah with 21 miniatures; no rubrications between f. 197v-373v.

author.name: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

respStmt.persName: Qummī, Muḥammad ibn Shaykh ʻAqīl al-Sharīf, active 1592
قمي، محمد بن شيخ عقيل الشريف،

supportDesc.extent: i, 385, i leaves : 353 x 217 (280 x 137) mm bound to 357 x 230 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left, some have been trimmed.

layoutDesc.layout: 33 lines in four columns; border-ruled and columns ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh with elements of nastaʻliq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated headpiece in blue, red and gold (f. 1v); 21 polychrome miniatures (f. 8r, 15v, 22v, 39r, 41r, 47r, 58r, 63v, 92v, 109v, 121v, 142v, 161v, 175r, 202r, 228v, 241r, 247r, 289v, 304r, 308v). Rubrications in red, blue, gold, and darker red; no rubrications between f. 197v-373v. Textblock border-ruled in gold, red and darker red.

binding.p: Bound in black leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II). Front covers have inlay gilded and red embossed floral central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces. Flap has matching design. Inside covers have bright red leather doublure with the same pattern as the outside covers recreated in green, blue, red, and black textile inlay with gold filigree overlay; a set of filigree cartouches in gold over pink, blue and green create a frame. The same filigree cartouches appear on the inside flap. Endbands in red and green.

origin.p: Copy completed by Muḥammad ibn Shaykh ʻAqīl al-Sharīf al-Qummī in Jumādá al-Ūlá in the months of the year after 1000 (February or March 1592 CE) (f. 385v).

history.provenance: Sold at the Ali Asghar Antiquatchi sale Anderson Auction Company (New York) 1-2 February, 1928, lot 251 (note in pencil on catalog entry pasted to first flyleaf recto). The note says 26 January, but the sale was in February of that year.
Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis.
